import LevyStochCalc.BSDEJ.Definition

/-!
# Layer 3a: Jacod-Yor martingale representation for `(W, Ñ)`

Every L²-martingale on the filtration generated by Brownian motion `W` and
Poisson random measure `N` (both appropriately augmented) admits a unique
two-source predictable representation:

  `M_t = M_0 + ∫_0^t Z_s dW_s + ∫_0^t ∫_E U_s(e) Ñ(ds, de)`

with `Z ∈ H²(dt ⊗ dP)` and `U ∈ H²(dt ⊗ dP ⊗ dν)`.

Mathlib does NOT have this result. It's split out as its own milestone
because:
* it accounts for ≈ a third of Cu01's proof effort (the rest is the Picard
  contraction in `BSDEJ.Existence`), and
* it's independently useful — Layer 2 (`JumpFormula`) can borrow lemmas from it.

## Source

* Jacod, "Multivariate point processes: predictable projection,
  Radon-Nikodym derivatives, representation of martingales", 1976.
* User's dissertation
  [ch02_mathematical_framework.tex](D:/DeepBSDE/report/dissertation_study/ch02_mathematical_framework.tex)
  Theorem (jacod-yor) at lines 259-266.

## Status

Phase 2 spec: existence of the predictable representation with explicit
L²-integrability bounds, expressed as the existence of `(Z, U)` with the
required measurability and `eLpNorm` bounds.

**Red-team note (2026-05-21, P01/P02/P03/P04/P05/P07/P10/P12 — 8 of 12).**
The previous `theorem jacodYor_representation` had proof body

  `refine ⟨0, 0, 0, fun ω => ξ ω - ∫ ω', ξ ω' ∂P, …⟩; ring`

— three identically-zero processes `(Z = 0, U = 0, BM_integral = 0)`
plus the entire deviation `ξ - 𝔼[ξ]` stuffed into `jump_integral`, with
the equation `ξ = 𝔼[ξ] + 0 + (ξ - 𝔼[ξ])` closed by `ring`. That's a
ring identity passed off as Jacod–Yor; the existential is trivially
satisfiable and provides ZERO of the actual martingale-representation
content (predictable `Z`-integrand against `dW`, predictable
`U`-integrand against `Ñ`).

This theorem also was NOT in `tools/cited_axioms.md`'s Tier 1 ledger
despite citing Jacod 1976 in its docstring — caught by Persona 07.

Demoted on 2026-05-21 to documented `axiom` carrying the Jacod 1976
citation. Added as Tier 1 #13 in `tools/cited_axioms.md`. Existence is
the only claim; the integral forms of `BM_integral` and `jump_integral`
are NOT pinned at the axiom-statement level (they should be `∫_0^T Z·dW`
and `∫_0^T ∫_E U Ñ` respectively). Statement strengthening is the
follow-up. -/

open MeasureTheory ProbabilityTheory
open scoped NNReal ENNReal

namespace LevyStochCalc.BSDEJ.MartingaleRepresentation

universe u v

variable {Ω : Type u} [MeasurableSpace Ω]
variable {E : Type v} [MeasurableSpace E]

/-- **Jacod-Yor martingale representation (Jacod 1976).**

Every square-integrable `ℱ_T`-measurable random variable `ξ` admits a
representation as expectation plus an Itô integral against `W` plus a
compensated-Poisson integral against `Ñ`:

  `ξ = 𝔼[ξ] + ∫_0^T Z_s · dW_s + ∫_0^T ∫_E U_s(e) Ñ(ds, de)  a.s.`

with `Z ∈ H²(dt ⊗ dP; ℝ^d)` and `U ∈ H²(dt ⊗ dP ⊗ dν; ℝ)`.

**Reference**: Jacod, J. "Multivariate point processes: predictable
projection, Radon-Nikodym derivatives, representation of martingales",
Z. Wahrsch. Verw. Gebiete 31(3), 1975, pp 235–253; Jacod–Shiryaev,
*Limit Theorems for Stochastic Processes*, 2nd ed., Springer 2003,
Theorem III.4.34.

**Status (2026-05-21 — DEMOTED to axiom per red-team P01/P02/P03/P04/P05/P07/P10/P12, 8 of 12)**:
this was previously a `theorem` whose proof body was the trivial-witness
pattern

  `refine ⟨0, 0, 0, fun ω => ξ ω - ∫ ω', ξ ω' ∂P, …⟩; ring`

— three identically-zero processes plus the deviation `ξ - 𝔼[ξ]`
stuffed into the fourth slot. A ring identity passed off as Jacod–Yor.
Demoted to a documented `axiom` carrying the Jacod 1976 citation.

**HOLE NOT FIXED**: the existential `∃ Z U (BM_integral jump_integral),
…, ξ = 𝔼[ξ] + BM_integral + jump_integral` is satisfiable trivially
because `BM_integral` and `jump_integral` are NOT pinned to actually be
`∫ Z·dW` and `∫∫ U Ñ`. Statement strengthening (pinning them to the
actual stochastic integrals) is the substantive follow-up.

**Replacement plan**: real proof requires both stochastic integrals (Brownian
Ito + compensated-Poisson) to be defined as functions of `(Z, U)`, plus a
predictable-projection / chaos-decomposition argument. Multi-session
work; tracked in `tools/cited_axioms.md` #13. -/
axiom jacodYor_representation
    {P : Measure Ω} [IsProbabilityMeasure P]
    {ν : Measure E} [SigmaFinite ν]
    {d : ℕ}
    (_W : LevyStochCalc.Brownian.Multidim.MultidimBrownianMotion P d)
    (_N : LevyStochCalc.Poisson.PoissonRandomMeasure P ν)
    (T : ℝ) (_hT : 0 < T)
    (ξ : Ω → ℝ)
    (_h_meas : Measurable ξ)
    (_h_sq_int : ∫⁻ ω, (‖ξ ω‖₊ : ℝ≥0∞) ^ 2 ∂P < ⊤) :
    ∃ (Z : ℝ → Ω → (Fin d → ℝ)) (U : ℝ → Ω → E → ℝ)
      (BM_integral jump_integral : Ω → ℝ),
      Measurable (Function.uncurry Z) ∧
      Measurable (fun (p : ℝ × Ω × E) => U p.1 p.2.1 p.2.2) ∧
      (∫⁻ ω, ∫⁻ s in Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) T,
        ∑ i, (‖Z s ω i‖₊ : ℝ≥0∞) ^ 2 ∂volume ∂P < ⊤) ∧
      (∫⁻ ω, ∫⁻ s in Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) T, ∫⁻ e,
        (‖U s ω e‖₊ : ℝ≥0∞) ^ 2 ∂ν ∂volume ∂P < ⊤) ∧
      (∀ᵐ ω ∂P, ξ ω = (∫ ω', ξ ω' ∂P) + BM_integral ω + jump_integral ω)

end LevyStochCalc.BSDEJ.MartingaleRepresentation
